alwaysApply: true
---

Use these rules for **borrower_pro (Demo_Client)** — the borrower-facing frontend for TrueKredit Pro. Borrowers register and borrow money online (digital license KPKT).

---

## 1) Context

- **Location**: `apps/borrower_pro/Demo_Client/` — client-specific app; template for new clients.
- **Shared components**: Live at `apps/borrower_pro/components/` (outside client folder). Import ShadCN, shared UI from there. Do not duplicate components in each client folder.
- **Backend**: `backend_pro` — Better Auth, borrower APIs.

---

## 2) Framework & Structure

- **Next.js 16.x** with App Router.
- TypeScript only.
- Organize by feature: `app/(auth)/sign-in`, `app/(auth)/sign-up`, `app/(dashboard)/` (future).
- Next.js 16 requires convention of proxy instead of middleware files.

---

## 3) Shared Components (No Duplication)

- **ShadCN UI** and other reusable components live at `apps/borrower_pro/components/`.
- Demo_Client imports from parent: use path alias or relative import to `../components`.
- Do **not** copy ShadCN or shared components into Demo_Client. Add new shared components to `apps/borrower_pro/components/` so all clients can use them.
- Client-specific code: branding, layout, theme, custom pages. Shared: forms, buttons, inputs, SignIn, SignUp flows.

---

## 4) Auth (Better Auth)

- Use **Better Auth** client for sign in / sign up (no admin plugin — borrower auth only).
- Session-based; cookies handled by Better Auth.
- Base URL = this app's URL (where auth API routes live). Auth routes at `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`.

```typescript
// Example: createAuthClient for borrower (no adminClient)
import { createAuthClient } from "better-auth/react";

export const authClient = createAuthClient({
  baseURL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL || "http://localhost:3001",
});
```

Auth API route: `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts` using `toNextJsHandler` from Better Auth. Backend_pro verifies sessions; BETTER_AUTH_SECRET must match.

---

## 5) UI System

- Use **ShadCN UI** from shared components.
- Use **sonner** for toasts.
- Modularize: `components/ui` (shared) vs `components/features/<feature>` (client-specific if needed).
- Refer to `docs/planning/brand.md` for Demo_Client branding.

---

## 6) Theming & Typography

- Support light/dark theme (configurable per client).
- Use fonts and colors from `brand.md`.
- Client-specific theming via CSS variables or theme provider.

### Colors — Do NOT Hardcode

**Never hardcode hex codes or Tailwind color names** (e.g. `#6151ca`, `red-500`, `emerald-500`, `amber-500`) in components. All brand/status colors are defined in one place: `app/globals.css`.

- **Use theme variables**: `primary`, `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info` (e.g. `text-error`, `bg-success/10`, `border-primary`).
- **Change once**: Update `app/globals.css` to update colors globally.
- See `docs/planning/brand.md` for the full color system.

---

## 7) Forms & Validation

- Schema-based validation (Zod).
- Inline validation with consistent error messaging.
- Accessible, keyboard-friendly inputs.

---

## 8) Date, Time & Number Formatting

- Database: UTC. Frontend: display in Malaysia timezone (GMT+8).
- Use `formatDate`, `formatCurrency`, etc. from `lib/utils.ts`.
- Use safe math utilities for any financial display.

---

## 9) Current Scope (Phase 1)

For now, focus on:
- **Sign in** — borrower logs in
- **Sign up** — borrower registers to become a borrower

Future: loan application, repayments, dashboard, etc.
